My beautiful bag is from @luli.bebe As a second time mom I knew I didn’t want to over pack. I’m so grateful that our hospital provides diapers, wipes, swaddles, pads, dermaplast, shower toiletries and a pump to use if needed. So I can pack the bare minimum. 
I packed 3 lounge sets, 4 baby outfits, slippers, robe and some of my own toiletries (body/face lotion/deodorant) for me husband and baby. Also threw my haaka in there. I’ll just add our toothbrushes, hair brushes and chargers the day I go into labor!
